1
00:00:00,234 --> 00:00:06,614
The architectural style of the Armenian Church relies on tall towers

2
00:00:06,639 --> 00:00:13,177
And on the spacious interiors that differ from other churches

3
00:00:13,542 --> 00:00:17,526
In addition to the conical dome present in the Armenian Church

4
00:00:17,551 --> 00:00:21,354
Which is similar in form to the Armenian Church in Baghdad

5
00:00:21,379 --> 00:00:23,385
Near Tayaran Square

6
00:00:23,410 --> 00:00:26,589
And many other Armenian churches

7
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:32,968
I think this style is the one followed in the churches of the capital Yerevan

8
00:00:32,993 --> 00:00:34,922
The churches of the Republic of Armenia

9
00:00:34,947 --> 00:00:40,651
In terms of design, it is a European style adopted in this architecture

10
00:00:41,438 --> 00:00:48,052
Interviewer: We are now outside the church. Can
you tell us about those carvings behind you?

11
00:00:48,730 --> 00:00:50,839
Can you describe them a little?

12
00:00:50,864 --> 00:00:55,865
These carvings reflect Moslawi architecture

13
00:00:55,890 --> 00:01:02,063
There is no specific Armenian feature in these engraved leaves

14
00:01:02,088 --> 00:01:05,032
And the distinctive decorations

15
00:01:05,214 --> 00:01: 07,662
They belong to the Moslawi architectural tradition

16
00:01:07,948 --> 00:01:12,375
But these inscriptions are in the Armenian language, along with the cross

17
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,849
And this is the Armenian cross

18
00:01:14,928 --> 00:01:18,938
ISIS distorted these inscriptions

19
00:01:18,963 --> 00:01:23,391
As well as the cross on the church façade

20
00:01:23,415 --> 00:01:30,421
But overall, the distinctive feature is that this is based on Moslawi architecture

21
00:01:30,446 --> 00:01:31,907
Known for its marble stone

22
00:01:31,932 --> 00:01:34,797
In the Moslawi architectural style

23
00:01:35,657 --> 00:01:37,922
Interviewer: What do these inscriptions mean?

24
00:01:37,947 --> 00:01:43,573
These inscriptions indicate that this is the Etchmiadzin Armenian Church

25
00:01:43,598 --> 00:01:48,026
Etchmiadzin is one of the well-known saints in the church

26
00:01:48,051 --> 00:01:53,131
Armenians always use the names of saints

27
00:01:53,156 --> 00:01:54,719
For their churches

28
00:01:54,744 --> 00:01:56,750
Like Etchmiadzin and Grigor

29
00:01:56,775 --> 00:02:01,309
And other names of saints known in Armenian history
